    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Alessandra Negro has been a ICU nurse for 15 years. At the moment she is the Nursing Coordinator of the heart surgery and functional rehabilitation Unit of the IRCCS San Raffaele Hospital, Milan, Italy, but for the pandemic emergency she was asked to coordinate a Covid ICU of the hospital. Matteo Cardinali and Roberta Ranzani are nurses working in neurosurgery unit, but for the pandemic emergency they worked in the Covid ICU.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Note",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "M. Mucci, P.Beccaria, G.Borghi, T.Capocasa, N.Pasculli are intensivist working in the general Intensive Care Unit of the IRCCS San Raffaele Hospital, Milan, Italy, during the pandemic emergency they worked in the Covid ICU.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Note",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Giulia Villa is a nurse coordinator of the IRCCS San Raffaele Hospital, during the pandemic emergency she helped to write and supervised the paper.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Note",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Prof. Alberto Zangrillo is the head of the Emergency Department, during the pandemic emergency he and his team created and managed four new covid ICUs.",
